<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="pb-brownies" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Peanut Butter Brownies</title>

  <p>
    Ingredients:
  </p>
  <tabular>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> cup peanut butter</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{3}</m> cup butter, softened</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{2}{3}</m> cup white sugar</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
    <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> cup packed brown sugar</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>2 large eggs</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{2}</m> teaspoon vanilla extract</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup all-purpose flour</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 teaspoon baking powder</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell><m>\frac{1}{4}</m> teaspoon salt</cell>
    </row>
    <row>
      <cell>1 cup chocolate chips (optional)</cell>
    </row>
  </tabular>

  <p>Instructions
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Cream together peanut butter and butter in a medium bowl. Gradually blend in white sugar, brown sugar, eggs, and vanilla; mix until fluffy.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Combine flour, baking powder, and salt in a separate bowl. Stir flour mixture and chocolate chips into the peanut butter mixture until well blended.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Spread mixture into 9" x 9" baking pan. Bake at <m>350^\circ</m> until the top springs back when touched, 35 minutes without chocolate chips, 40 minutes with chocolate chips. Cool and cut into 16 squares.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>

  <p>
    Notes:
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </p>
</section>